<TITLE> GM of garment factory takes shelter at police station </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  A general manager of a garment factory was chased into Uttara Police Station by the workers on Sunday as he reportedly had beaten a colleague. Uttara Police Station sub-inspector Faruque Bhuiyan told bdnews24.com Altaf Hossain, general manager of Pallmall Garment Factory at Uttara, took shelter there shortly before 10am. Since then some 700 workers took position in front of the police statio, blocking traffic on the Airport Road. The workers alleged that the general manager had been misbehaving with them for long. Altaf allegedly beat a female worker at around 9am, prompting the angry workers to chase him. At one stage he managed to quit the factory and took refuge at the police station, Faruque said. The workers got the information and took position there. They demanded punishment of the general manager. The representatives of the owners and workers sat in a meeting to reach an agreement. According to the police officer, Altaf told them that the workers had brought false allegations against him and that he had not beaten anybody. As he attempted to take action against them on charges of negligence of duties, they became furious. b
